column30: Entered as William BEARE dwelling in Yeldon was marryed to Elizabeth BARCOCK daughter of Hugh BARCOCK of Yeldon. Only 1623 is given as a date.
Etheldreda Anglice Audrie; Lamplugh has initials S.T.B following the name
Register states they were clandestinely married as they pretend at Stowe Longa Hunts. No date is given but BT indicates a date of 1671-1672.
This entry only appears in the B.T. and describes Grace as the daughter of George BARRATT of Melchbourne.
The B.T. has FAWSKETT and occurs for 04 Oct 1687.
No bride's name given; possibly Jane from marriage on 03 Sep 1711
Register states Mem. Ridley Browne was married in April last out of this parish.

Mem.  Richard Samworth was married out of this parish this date as I am told by himself and his Parents haveing no Certificate of ye same. B.T adds: by one Draper as at a licensed place without licence or bans published.

Mem.  William Long altered from Lug to Long in a different ink and Elizabeth Alphin both fellow servants of this Towne are sayd to have been married at.Kesoe Keysoe as William Lug confessed before me this dayshewing me a pretended certificate without No
The Register states: were married with a licence the fourteenth of February before ye morning service.

Dorothy Joyce and Thomas Cox shee a widdow of this parish and he of Puddington parish are sayd to be clandestinely married by Mr Draper and cohabit here as man and wife and shee owned ye marriage to myselfe but have no Certificate however secure ye Queen's duty thy say they were married
Register states: he a day labourer being fellow servants last yeare both guilty of antenuptiall fornication. Bedford Court to be certified thereof ex debito.
Bridget is described as his wife.
Elizabeth is described as his wife.
